

usually use in simple present sentences.
they come befor main verb or after to be verbs.





            Never-0     Rarly/Hardly ever -5     seldom     Occasionally-30     Sometimes-50        Often-70        Normally/Generally-80       Usaually-90      Always-100





I never call my friends at night.

You rarly play soccer on street.

He seldom works on the weekends.

She occasionally participates in meetings.





    point ==> use "never" always in pasitive sentences(positive verb)
    point ==> you can use "sometimes,often,usually" in first of sentences, but others can't be used in first of sentences.



Sometimes, I walk in the park.

Often, he stays up late.

Usually, we read a book befor going to bed.
